Police say they have specific leads in the death of a 5-year-old boy from Lavender Hill in Cape Town. He was shot dead yesterday. In the same area, a 22-year-old man was shot in the chest. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The family of five-year-old Valentino Grootetjie will be spending Christmas without their son. Grootetjie was shot dead on Saturday in his backyard in Lavender Hill in Cape Town. His family wants justice. “I was inside the house with my baby. I saw everything. I hope the lord will get them...for what they done to my son. They will pay,” said Valentino's mother, Romana. READ: Five-year-old boy shot dead in Lavender Hill Police are investigating whether the two shootings are gang-related. In the same area, a 22-year-old man was shot in the chest.